        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(active-memory): exclude dreaming-narrative session keys from interactive eligibility gate",
        "body": "## Root Cause\n\nActive-memory's `isEligibleInteractiveSession` accepted dreaming-narrative cron session keys because they share `trigger=\"user\"` with real conversational sessions. Each false-accepted invocation paid the full active-memory cold-start cost inside a hardcoded 45000ms command-lane budget, reliably causing timeouts during cron windows.\n\nAdditionally, the initial regex guard used a broad colon-delimited match (`/(?:^|:)dreaming-narrative-(?:light|rem|deep)-/i`) that could false-positive on real chat session IDs whose peer ID happens to contain a phased dreaming-narrative prefix (e.g. `agent:main:webchat:dreaming-narrative-light-room`).\n\n## Summary\n\n- Added a guard clause that returns `false` when the session key matches canonical dreaming-narrative patterns (bare `dreaming-narrative-<phase>-<hash>` or agent-prefixed `agent:<agentId>:dreaming-narrative-<phase>-<hash>`).\n- Anchored the regex to match only the canonical key shapes instead of any colon-delimited segment, preventing false rejection of real chat keys like `agent:main:webchat:dreaming-narrative-light-room`.\n- Added a regression test for a webchat session key whose peer ID starts with a phased dreaming-narrative prefix.\n- Fixes #78500\n\n## Verification\n\n- `pnpm test extensions/active-memory` — 151 tests passed (150 existing + 1 new regression test)\n- 3 dreaming-related tests all pass:\n  - does not run for dreaming-narrative cron session keys\n  - allows non-canonical session keys that merely contain the dreaming-narrative substring\n  - allows real webchat session keys whose peer id starts with a phased dreaming-narrative prefix\n- Autoreview: pending (new commit pushed)\n- CI: pending\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: Active-memory eligibility gate correctly rejects canonical dreaming-narrative session keys while allowing real chat session keys whose peer ID starts with a phased dreaming-narrative prefix. Regex narrowed from broad colon-delimited match to canonical key-shape match.\n\nReal environment tested: Linux (x86_64), Node v24.13.1, OpenClaw 2026.6.2 (72a8d4c), branch `fix/active-memory-dreaming-gate`.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch:\n```bash\npnpm build\npnpm openclaw --version\npnpm test extensions/active-memory/index.test.ts -- -t dreaming\npnpm test extensions/active-memory/index.test.ts\n```\n\nEvidence after fix:\n```\n$ pnpm openclaw --version\nOpenClaw 2026.6.2 (72a8d4c)\n\n$ pnpm test extensions/active-memory/index.test.ts -- -t dreaming\n\n RUN  v4.1.7 /home/0668000452/codes/OPENSOURCES/openclaw\n\n Test Files  1 passed (1)\n      Tests  3 passed | 148 skipped (151)\n\n$ pnpm test extensions/active-memory/index.test.ts\n\n Test Files  1 passed (1)\n      Tests  151 passed (151)\n```\n\nObserved result after fix: The dreaming guard correctly excludes `agent:main:dreaming-narrative-light-abc123` (canonical dreaming key) while allowing `agent:main:webchat:dreaming-narrative-light-room` (real chat peer ID with phased prefix). The old regex incorrectly rejected the latter. Build binary (OpenClaw 2026.6.2) matches HEAD commit (72a8d4c).\n\nWhat was not tested: Full cron-window runtime simulation. The fix is validated through the active-memory test suite which exercises the `before_prompt_build` hook path with both canonical dreaming keys and real chat session keys. A live gateway/cron-window test would provide additional confidence but the unit-level test coverage directly validates the eligibility logic boundary.\n",
